  "body": "The BftMiningCoordinator has a shutdown method to stop processing of events by stopping the BftProcessor and BftExecutors. This doesn't work if it is called from the same Thread as the BftMiningCoordinator is running on.\n\n**Acceptance Critieria**\n* BftMiningCoordinator can stop regardless of what the calling thread is\n\n**How To Reproduce**\n\n1. Set a single node IBFT to QBFT migration\n2. Have a migration to the QBFT\n3. The BftMiningCoordinator should attempt to shutdown the IBFT BftMiningCoordinator\n4. At this point the we fail to migrate due the shutdown hanging\n\n**Notes**\n* The MigratingMiningCoordinator calls the stop method on the BftMiningCoordinators when the migration is reached. This happens in the onBlockAdded method.\n* It's important that the stop method remains synchronous",
